aVBut it's worth recalling Wittgenstein's remark on the subject:
p68
aV"Tell me," he asked a friend, "why do people always say
p69
aVit was natural for man to assume that the Sun went 'round the Earth,
p70
aVrather than that the Earth was rotating?"
p71
aVAnd his friend replied, "Well, obviously,
p72
aVbecause it just looks as though the Sun is going round the Earth."
p73
aVWittgenstein replied, "Well, what would it have looked like
p74
