aVAs an evolutionary biologist, I'd say this: our brains have evolved
p89
aVto help us survive within the orders of magnitude, of size and speed
p90
aVwhich our bodies operate at.
p91
aVWe never evolved to navigate in the world of atoms.
p92
aVIf we had, our brains probably would perceive rocks
p93
aVas full of empty space.
p94
