aa(lp214
VSo "really" isn't a word that we should use with simple confidence.
p215
aVIf a neutrino had a brain,
p216
aVwhich it evolved in neutrino-sized ancestors,
p217
aVit would say that rocks really do consist of empty space.
p218
aVWe have brains that evolved in medium-sized ancestors
p219
aVwhich couldn't walk through rocks.
p220
aV"Really," for an animal, is whatever its brain needs it to be
p221
aVin order to assist its survival.
p222
aVAnd because different species live in different worlds,
p223
aVthere will be a discomforting variety of "reallys."
p224
aVWhat we see of the real world is not the unvarnished world,
p225
aVbut a model of the world, regulated and adjusted by sense data,
p226
aVbut constructed so it's useful for dealing with the real world.
p227
